<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 17 at 6:15PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
southwestern Giles, northeastern Tazewell, Bland and southern Mercer
Counties through 645 PM EDT...
At 615 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Bluefield, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Bluefield...
Bland...
Rocky Gap...
Bastian...
Pocahontas...
Oakvale...
and Ceres.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
